<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1955,2018]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,150,213]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="105" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius, C." box="[151,355,1955,1981]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="409 - 421" refId="ref4204" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1900) Verzeichniss der von Dr. F. Meinert im Jahre 1891 in Venezuela gesammelten Cerambyciden. Ofversigt Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 57, 409 - 421." type="journal article" year="1900">Aurivillius (1900)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[478,604,1955,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecilus">
<emphasis box="[478,604,1955,1982]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">C. poecilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<typeStatus box="[719,817,1956,1982]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">syntypes</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[886,1005,1955,1981]" name="Venezuela" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[1089,1289,1955,1981]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="285 - 288" refId="ref4726" refString="Breuning, S. (1971 b) Neue Lamiinae aus den Bestanden des Zoologischen Museums der Humboldt-Universitat in Berlin (Col., Cerambycidae). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 47 (2), 285 - 288. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19710470206" type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971b)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columbianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B. columbianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[364,478,1991,2017]" name="Colombia" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. Comparing the photographs of a 
<typeStatus box="[861,948,1992,2018]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">syntype</typeStatus>
of the former (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1202,1991,2017]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–35. 27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[204,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[200,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 27–35. 27) Bisaltes buquetii Thomson, 1868, holotype female. 28) Bisaltes triangularis Breuning, 1940, holotype. 29) Bisaltes flaviceps Breuning, 1940, holotype. 30–31) Bisaltes fuscodiscalis Breuning, 1943, holotype female: 30) Dorsal habitus; 31) Basal antennomeres. 32) Bisaltes (Craspedocerus) ptericoptoides Breuning, 1942, holotype 33) Bisaltes pictus Breuning, 1940, holotype. 34) Craspedocerus poecilus Aurivillius, 1900, syntype male. 35) Bisaltes columbianus Breuning, 1971, holotype. Figures 27–34 by Jesus Santiago Moure; figure 35 by John Chemsak." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825637/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) and the 
<typeStatus box="[1307,1405,1991,2017]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">holotype</typeStatus>
of the latter (
<figureCitation box="[265,348,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–35. 27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[204,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[200,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 27–35. 27) Bisaltes buquetii Thomson, 1868, holotype female. 28) Bisaltes triangularis Breuning, 1940, holotype. 29) Bisaltes flaviceps Breuning, 1940, holotype. 30–31) Bisaltes fuscodiscalis Breuning, 1943, holotype female: 30) Dorsal habitus; 31) Basal antennomeres. 32) Bisaltes (Craspedocerus) ptericoptoides Breuning, 1942, holotype 33) Bisaltes pictus Breuning, 1940, holotype. 34) Craspedocerus poecilus Aurivillius, 1900, syntype male. 35) Bisaltes columbianus Breuning, 1971, holotype. Figures 27–34 by Jesus Santiago Moure; figure 35 by John Chemsak." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825637/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="105">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
), we conclude that they belong to the same species. Therefore, we synonymize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columbianus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[1234,1323,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="105">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1338,1427,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="105">Bisaltes</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,294,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="105">columbianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[358,742,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecilus" subGenus="Craspedocerus">
<emphasis box="[358,447,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="105">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[463,633,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="105">Craspedocerus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[649,742,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="105">poecilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
